  "description": "Kurt Johan Bergström was a Swedish MD and chief county medical officer in Jönköping. He was born on July 23, 1891 in Lidingö to agronomist R.A.B. and Lovisa Bergman. Bergström had two marriages and three children named Marianne, Marguerite, and Inga Brita. He got his high school exam in 1910 and finished his Bachelor of Medicine, Licentiate of Medicine, and Doctorate of Medicine in Stockholm University in 1915, 1920, and 1936 respectively. Bergström had various roles in the medical field such as Assistant Physician, Marine Medical Officer, and Provinsialläkare. He also became a member of board of directors for Visby hospital and state institution for epileptic patients in Jönköping. Bergström received several honors and awards throughout his career." 
